Privacy Policy for NoTrack Extension

Last Updated: 06/04/2025

1. Introduction
NoTrack is a privacy-focused browser extension that helps protect your privacy by detecting and blocking web trackers while monitoring website security status. We are committed to transparency and protecting your privacy.

2. Information Collection and Use
Our extension processes the following types of data:

a) Website URLs and Network Requests
- We analyze website URLs and network requests to detect tracking scripts
- This analysis happens entirely within your browser
- No URLs or website data is stored permanently
- All data is cleared automatically when you close browser tabs

b) Tracker Detection Data
- We maintain a temporary list of detected trackers per tab
- This data exists only in your browser's memory
- Data is automatically cleared when tabs are closed
- No tracking data is transmitted externally

3. Data Storage
- All processing occurs locally in your browser
- No data is stored permanently
- No information is sent to external servers
- All temporary data is cleared when closing tabs

4. Data Sharing
- We do not collect, store, or share any user data
- No information is transmitted to third parties
- All tracker detection happens locally in your browser

5. Your Privacy Rights
- The extension operates entirely locally on your device
- You can disable or remove the extension at any time
- No personal data is collected or stored
- No data persistence between browser sessions

6. Security
- All operations are performed locally in your browser
- No external servers are contacted
- No data is transmitted over the internet
- Your browsing data remains private and secure

7. Children's Privacy
Our extension does not collect any personal information from any users, including children under 13 years of age.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected with an updated date at the top of this policy.

9. Contact Information
For questions or concerns about this privacy policy, please contact:
[Your Contact Information]

10. Compliance
This extension is designed with privacy as its core principle and complies with major privacy regulations including GDPR and CCPA.
